Package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.storage

Class DataExtractorsUi

java.lang.Object
io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.storage.DataExtractorsUi
public class DataExtractorsUi extends Object
Utility class providing data extraction mechanisms for UI-related data storage and retrieval.

This class contains static methods for extracting data from API responses and table elements. It provides functionalities to:

  • Extract JSON data from stored API responses.
  • Retrieve specific table rows based on search criteria or index.
  • Process and filter data for validation and assertions.

    • responseBodyExtraction

      public static <T> io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.storage.DataExtractor<T> responseBodyExtraction(String responsePrefix, String jsonPath, int index)
      Creates a DataExtractor to retrieve a value from a stored API response body using a JSONPath expression.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The expected return type of the extracted data.
      Parameters:
      responsePrefix - The prefix of the API response URL used to filter relevant responses.
      jsonPath - The JSONPath expression used to extract data from the response body.
      index - The index (from the most recent) of the filtered API responses to extract data from.
      Returns:
      A DataExtractor that retrieves the specified value from the API response.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If the provided index is out of range.

    • tableRowExtractor

      public static <T> io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.storage.DataExtractor<T> tableRowExtractor(Enum<?> key, String... indicators)
      Creates a DataExtractor to retrieve a specific table row from storage based on search criteria.

      This method searches stored table data for a row containing all specified indicator values. It compares row values case-insensitively after trimming whitespace.

      Type Parameters:
      T - The expected return type of the extracted table row.
      Parameters:
      key - The key used to retrieve the stored table data.
      indicators - The values used to search for a matching row.
      Returns:
      A DataExtractor that retrieves the matching row from the table.

    • tableRowExtractor

      public static <T> io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.storage.DataExtractor<T> tableRowExtractor(Enum<?> key, int index)
      Creates a DataExtractor to retrieve a specific table row from storage based on its index.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The expected return type of the extracted table row.
      Parameters:
      key - The key used to retrieve the stored table data.
      index - The zero-based index of the row to retrieve.
      Returns:
      A DataExtractor that retrieves the row at the specified index.
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the index is out of range.
